WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.786
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03.916 --> 00:06.093
"BAYWATCH DOWN UNDER PART ONE"

00:13.970 --> 00:15.015
ANYTHING?

00:15.145 --> 00:15.928
NOTHING!

00:16.059 --> 00:17.452
I DON'T SEE ANYBODY!

00:17.582 --> 00:18.670
KEEP LOOKING!

00:18.801 --> 00:21.412
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

00:30.726 --> 00:31.509
ANYTHING?

00:31.640 --> 00:32.683
NOTHING!

00:32.815 --> 00:33.772
I DON'T SEE ANYBODY.

00:33.903 --> 00:35.122
KEEP LOOKING!

00:35.252 --> 00:37.298
WATCH THE CURRENT, GUYS,
IT'S REALLY STRONG,

00:37.428 --> 00:38.864
I'M GETTING PULLED ALL OVER.

00:40.214 --> 00:44.435
[MUFFLED GRUNTING]

00:49.788 --> 00:51.529
I FOUND THE CAR,
HE'S RIGHT HERE!

00:52.661 --> 00:53.792
MITCH!

00:54.750 --> 00:56.099
LET'S GET HIM!

00:59.929 --> 01:04.586
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

01:28.131 --> 01:30.351
EASY, EASY, SUPPORT HIS HEAD.

01:30.481 --> 01:31.830
GOT HIM?

01:31.961 --> 01:33.615
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GET HIM IN.

01:34.616 --> 01:36.226
CHRIS, GET READY, MAN.

01:36.357 --> 01:38.141
IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT,
EASY, EASY.

01:38.272 --> 01:40.578
WATCH HIS NECK.
POSSIBLE SPINAL INJURY.

01:42.145 --> 01:43.799
-EVERYBODY HERE?
-YEAH.

01:43.929 --> 01:46.845
THAT'S GOOD.
ALL RIGHT, GOOD JOB, GUYS.

01:46.976 --> 01:48.108
YEAH.

01:48.238 --> 01:50.675
WAIT A MINUTE, WHERE'S JAKE?

01:50.806 --> 01:52.112
-WHAT?
-ANYONE SEE JAKE?

01:52.242 --> 01:53.939
-I DON'T SEE HIM.
-JAKE!

01:54.897 --> 01:57.334
LIFEGUARD DOWN!
HIT THE WATER WITH THE LIGHTS!

01:59.510 --> 02:00.511
JAKE?

02:00.642 --> 02:01.643
JAKE?

02:07.649 --> 02:08.866
JAKE?

02:10.173 --> 02:11.348
JAKE!

02:12.523 --> 02:13.350
JAKE!

02:13.481 --> 02:16.136
COME ON, JAKE, COME ON, MAN.

02:18.050 --> 02:20.792
CAREFUL, THE CURRENT'S TRICKY!

02:20.923 --> 02:24.231
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

02:42.553 --> 02:44.164
MITCH, YOU SEE ANYTHING?

03:35.606 --> 03:37.304
ARE YOU OKAY?

03:37.434 --> 03:40.176
IT WAS BAD, HAD ME PINNED,
I COULDN'T GET OUT.

03:40.307 --> 03:41.525
COME ON,
LET'S GET A BLANKET ON HIM.

03:41.656 --> 03:42.961
WHAT ABOUT THE GUY IN THE CAR?

03:43.092 --> 03:44.311
HE'S ON THE WAY TO THE HOSPITAL.

03:44.441 --> 03:46.530
HE'S GONNA BE FINE.

03:46.661 --> 03:47.618
THANKS.

03:47.749 --> 03:49.011
IT'S ALL PART OF THE SERVICE,
PAL.

03:49.141 --> 03:51.100
THIS TIME I GOT YOU,
NEXT TIME YOU GET ME, EH?

03:51.231 --> 03:53.363
LET'S GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE,
I'M FREEZING.

03:53.494 --> 03:56.410
[OPENING THEME SONG]

04:01.502 --> 04:04.853
♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

04:04.983 --> 04:08.857
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

04:08.987 --> 04:12.904
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HAVE SOMEBODY ♪

04:13.035 --> 04:16.647
♪ WITH THE EDGE OF SURRENDER
IN SIGHT ♪

04:16.778 --> 04:19.433
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

04:19.563 --> 04:21.738
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT

04:24.960 --> 04:26.570
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

04:26.701 --> 04:30.661
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

04:33.795 --> 04:37.581
♪ I'LL BE READY, I'LL BE READY

04:37.712 --> 04:41.542
♪ NEVER YOUR FEAR,
NO DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

04:41.672 --> 04:44.632
♪ I'LL BE READY

04:44.762 --> 04:47.809
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

04:47.939 --> 04:50.855
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

04:54.903 --> 04:57.297
BAYWATCH

05:02.519 --> 05:03.825
MAN, I AM SO FREEZING.

05:03.955 --> 05:06.001
OH, AS SOON AS I GET WARMED UP,

05:06.131 --> 05:08.569
I AM GONNA HAVE TO PLOT
A MAJOR INCIDENT REPORT.

05:08.699 --> 05:10.571
WELL,
WHEN I WOKE UP THIS MORNING,

05:10.701 --> 05:11.833
I HAD A FEELING
THAT SOMETHING TERRIBLE

05:11.963 --> 05:13.051
WAS GONNA HAPPEN.

05:13.182 --> 05:15.140
I THOUGHT I'D BOUGHT IT.

05:15.271 --> 05:18.274
IF YOU HADN'T COME AND GOT ME,
I'M DONE.

05:18.405 --> 05:20.581
YOU MUST HAVE BEEN TERRIFIED.

05:20.711 --> 05:21.538
SHE'S A ROOKIE.

05:21.669 --> 05:23.801
YUP.

05:23.932 --> 05:26.456
JESSIE, THIS IS JAKE BARNES,
USUALLY WORKS UP AT ZUMA BEACH.

05:27.892 --> 05:29.720
JESSIE, YOU STAY A LIFEGUARD
LONG ENOUGH,

05:29.851 --> 05:31.505
ONE DAY YOU'RE GONNA BE
WHERE I WAS TONIGHT.

05:31.635 --> 05:33.942
YOUR LIFEGUARD TRAINING
KICKS IN.

05:34.072 --> 05:35.596
YOU KNOW WHAT IT TELLS YOU?

05:35.726 --> 05:36.510
DON'T PANIC?

05:36.640 --> 05:37.772
EXACTLY.

05:37.902 --> 05:40.514
I BECAME INCREDIBLY CALM,
MY MIND WAS CLEAR,

05:40.644 --> 05:42.603
CLEARER THAN IT'S EVER BEEN.

05:42.733 --> 05:45.127
AND I KNOW THAT THERE WAS BACKUP
RIGHT THERE.

05:45.257 --> 05:46.868
ALL I HAD TO DO
WAS SHAKE THE TREE,

05:46.998 --> 05:48.260
SOMEBODY WOULD COME GET ME.

05:49.436 --> 05:50.698
JAKE.

05:53.527 --> 05:56.094
ERIC. WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

05:56.225 --> 05:57.792
WE NEED TO TALK.

05:58.488 --> 05:59.663
GET OUTTA HERE.

05:59.794 --> 06:01.622
WE GOT NOTHING TO TALK ABOUT.

06:03.667 --> 06:04.929
CAN I SEE YOU IN PRIVATE?

06:05.060 --> 06:06.975
YOU WANNA STEP OUTSIDE, ERIC?

06:07.105 --> 06:08.672
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, GO EASY, JAKE.

06:09.456 --> 06:10.979
NO, THAT'S COOL, CODY.

06:12.720 --> 06:15.418
ERIC HERE IS MY EX-WIFE'S
OLD BOYFRIEND

06:15.549 --> 06:16.941
AND CURRENT LAWYER.

06:17.768 --> 06:19.466
SAY WHAT YOU CAME TO SAY.

06:23.078 --> 06:24.514
CLAIRE'S DEAD.

06:26.908 --> 06:31.173
[SAD MUSIC PLAYING]

06:39.703 --> 06:41.096
OH NO.

06:45.143 --> 06:46.057
HOW?

06:47.319 --> 06:48.495
A TRAFFIC ACCIDENT.

06:56.633 --> 06:59.549
ALL RIGHT, YOU TOLD ME,
NOW GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE.

06:59.680 --> 07:01.116
NO, THERE'S SOMETHING ELSE.

07:02.291 --> 07:04.728
WHAT ELSE
COULD THERE POSSIBLY BE, ERIC?

07:05.512 --> 07:06.817
A CHILD.

07:09.472 --> 07:10.430
A CHILD?

07:17.001 --> 07:18.089
HE'S YOUR SON.

07:19.961 --> 07:21.571
AND HIS NAME'S TERENCE.

07:24.139 --> 07:26.184
THAT WAS MY FATHER'S NAME.

07:35.280 --> 07:36.891
THERE'S AN ADDRESS ON THE BACK.

07:40.721 --> 07:42.462
WHAT DO YOU EXPECT ME TO DO?

07:43.550 --> 07:44.768
DO?

07:46.335 --> 07:50.426
DO WHAT YOU ALWAYS DO, JAKE,
RUN AWAY.

08:30.814 --> 08:32.337
CLAIRE'S DEAD.

08:47.701 --> 08:49.006
HEY, BUD.

08:51.705 --> 08:53.054
HEARD ABOUT YOUR LOSS.

08:55.491 --> 08:56.797
DIDN'T KNOW YOU WERE MARRIED.

08:59.190 --> 09:01.018
A FEW YEARS BACK I WAS BEATING
AROUND THE WORLD,

09:01.149 --> 09:02.846
SURFING, GOOFING OFF.

09:04.805 --> 09:09.200
MET THIS GIRL IN SYDNEY,
THIS INCREDIBLE GIRL, CLAIRE.

09:09.984 --> 09:12.073
ANYWAY, WE GOT MARRIED
BUT IT DIDN'T WORK OUT.

09:12.682 --> 09:15.816
MY FAULT.
I JUST WASN'T WHAT SHE WANTED.

09:16.773 --> 09:18.209
SO I LEFT.

09:18.340 --> 09:20.603
I COULD NEVER BRING MYSELF
TO SIGN THE DIVORCE PAPERS,

09:20.734 --> 09:21.996
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT
ERIC WAS HERE FOR.

09:23.824 --> 09:25.956
SEE, I NEVER STOPPED LOVING HER,
MITCH,

09:27.262 --> 09:28.829
I ALWAYS FIGURED SOMEHOW,
SOMEDAY,

09:28.959 --> 09:31.005
I WAS GONNA END UP
BACK IN SYDNEY.

09:31.135 --> 09:33.442
THAT WE WERE GONNA END UP
BACK TOGETHER.

09:33.573 --> 09:36.576
NOW, THIS, A CHILD, A SON.

09:38.316 --> 09:39.796
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

09:39.927 --> 09:41.493
NO, YOU KNOW EXACTLY WHAT TO DO.

09:41.624 --> 09:43.931
YEAH, GET ON A PLANE TO SYDNEY,
THEN WHAT?

09:44.061 --> 09:45.889
SEE YOUR SON,
TAKE IT FROM THERE.

09:46.020 --> 09:47.369
WHAT, BECOME SOMEONE'S FATHER?

09:47.499 --> 09:50.894
JAKE, IT'S TIME TO GROW UP, MAN.

09:52.461 --> 09:55.072
LOOK, A FEW YEARS BACK,
THE SAME THING HAPPENED TO ME.

09:55.203 --> 09:57.118
DIFFERENT SITUATION,
BUT THE SAME.

09:58.293 --> 09:59.468
HOBIE NEEDED ME.

10:00.512 --> 10:02.950
I DIDN'T KNOW IF I COULD DO IT,
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT,

10:03.080 --> 10:05.213
I KNEW I HAD TO TRY.

10:05.343 --> 10:07.476
LET ME TELL YOU, MAN,
IT'S BEEN THE MOST AWESOME,

10:07.607 --> 10:10.261
INCREDIBLE, FRUSTRATING,
DEMANDING EXPERIENCE OF MY LIFE

10:10.392 --> 10:12.568
WATCHING THAT LITTLE BOY
GROW UP,

10:12.699 --> 10:14.875
TURNING INTO A MAN
AND ME BEING A PART OF THAT.

10:15.658 --> 10:17.007
YOU AND I ARE DIFFERENT, MITCH.

10:17.138 --> 10:18.530
YEAH, WE'RE DIFFERENT,
BUT WE'RE THE SAME.

10:18.661 --> 10:20.228
PEOPLE ARE IN TROUBLE,
WE RUN TO HELP THEM.

10:20.358 --> 10:21.403
YEAH, IN THE WATER.

10:21.533 --> 10:23.100
SOMEONE I DON'T KNOW,
A STRANGER,

10:23.231 --> 10:24.580
I'M GOOD WITH STRANGERS

10:24.711 --> 10:26.713
BECAUSE I CAN PULL 'EM OUT
AND I CAN WALK AWAY.

10:26.843 --> 10:28.105
DON'T WALK AWAY FROM THIS ONE.

10:31.108 --> 10:34.764
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT,
I'LL GO WITH YOU.

10:34.895 --> 10:35.765
TO AUSTRALIA?

10:35.896 --> 10:37.027
I GOT SOME VACATION TIME,

10:37.158 --> 10:38.289
I HEAR THE AIRLINE DEALS
ARE GREAT.

10:39.247 --> 10:40.727
I CAN'T ASK YOU TO DO THAT,
MITCH.

10:40.857 --> 10:44.078
YOU'RE NOT ASKING ME,
JUST USING YOU AN EXCUSE.

10:45.122 --> 10:46.602
I LOVE SYDNEY,

10:46.733 --> 10:49.300
IT'S ONE OF THE MOST AWESOME
CITIES ON THE PLANET.

10:59.920 --> 11:02.531
[PHONE RINGS]

11:05.360 --> 11:06.187
HELLO?

11:06.317 --> 11:07.971
HEY, KIP, IT'S BUCHANNON.

11:08.102 --> 11:09.538
MITCH, HOW ARE YOU?

11:09.669 --> 11:10.626
NEVER HAD A BETTER DAY.

11:10.757 --> 11:11.714
LISTEN, PAL,
I'M COMING DOWN UNDER,

11:11.845 --> 11:13.150
I'D LIKE TO GET TOGETHER.

11:13.281 --> 11:15.370
THAT'S STUPENDOUS,
YOUR TIMING COULDN'T BE BETTER.

11:16.414 --> 11:19.766
MITCH, LISTEN TO THIS,
I'M GOING TO BE A RACE PROMOTER.

11:19.896 --> 11:21.419
HOW'S THIS SOUND,

11:21.550 --> 11:23.291
A SERIES OF INTERNATIONAL
COMPETITIONS

11:23.421 --> 11:26.207
LIKE THE RYDER CUP
FOR WATER SPORTS.

11:26.337 --> 11:29.558
AMERICA, BRAZIL, HAWAII,
SOUTH AFRICA.

11:29.689 --> 11:32.126
BIG SPONSORS, BIG PRIZES.

11:32.256 --> 11:34.041
WELL, GOOD LUCK.

11:34.171 --> 11:35.390
WELL,
SINCE YOU'RE COMING ANYWAY,

11:35.520 --> 11:36.957
BRING YOUR US TEAM.

11:37.087 --> 11:38.785
YOU KNOW, I'D REALLY LIKE
TO HELP YOU GUYS OUT,

11:38.915 --> 11:40.656
BUT I'VE HAD A ROUGH SUMMER,
I'VE HAD ALL THE EXCITEMENT

11:40.787 --> 11:42.092
I NEED FOR A WHILE.

11:42.223 --> 11:44.747
WHAT IF I ARRANGE
TO FLY YOU DOWN

11:44.878 --> 11:45.966
ON AIR NEW ZEALAND?

11:46.096 --> 11:48.403
THE FINEST SERVICE
TO THE SOUTH PACIFIC.

11:49.360 --> 11:50.840
PUT YOU UP AT STAR CITY,

11:50.971 --> 11:54.235
SYDNEY'S BEAUTIFUL NEW CASINO
AT NO CHARGE TO YOU.

11:55.062 --> 11:56.237
SOUNDING BETTER.

11:56.367 --> 11:57.412
PUT SOME PEOPLE TOGETHER.

11:57.542 --> 12:00.763
ANOTHER GUY,
A COUPLE OF FEMALES.

12:00.894 --> 12:04.027
UH, WHAT KIND OF RACE
ARE WE TALKING ABOUT?

12:04.158 --> 12:08.336
IT'S A HYBRID, PART ECHO STYLE,
PART IRONMAN,

12:08.466 --> 12:09.816
A LITTLE TRIATHLON.

12:09.946 --> 12:11.643
STARTS IN SYDNEY,
ENDS IN THE BUSH.

12:11.774 --> 12:14.429
BIG ADVENTURE,
PERFECT FOR TELEVISION.

12:14.559 --> 12:16.474
I DUNNO, PAL, IT SOUNDS
LIKE A LITTLE BIT MORE

12:16.605 --> 12:18.085
THAN I WANNA TAKE ON.

12:18.215 --> 12:19.042
NO WORRIES.

12:19.173 --> 12:20.391
WE DON'T EXPECT YOU TO WIN.

12:20.522 --> 12:21.566
YOU DON'T?

12:21.697 --> 12:23.917
NO,
JUST SHOW UP AND LOOK THE PART.

12:24.047 --> 12:27.181
THE TRUTH IS, AGAINST THIS
AWESOME TEAM I PUT TOGETHER.

12:27.311 --> 12:29.270
YOU DON'T HAVE IT.

12:29.400 --> 12:30.184
REALLY?

12:30.314 --> 12:31.576
ABSOLUTELY.

12:31.707 --> 12:33.622
WE JUST NEED
A PRESENTABLE VICTIM.

12:33.753 --> 12:34.884
THAT'S WHY YOU'RE PERFECT.

12:35.015 --> 12:35.842
BECAUSE I CAN'T WIN?

12:35.972 --> 12:37.495
EXACTLY.

12:38.192 --> 12:39.802
SOUND LIKE WE SHOULD GO
TO AUSTRALIA.

12:42.500 --> 12:43.327
WE'RE IN!

12:43.458 --> 12:45.765
WOO! STUPENDOUS.

12:45.895 --> 12:47.897
HOW MANY ARE COMING?

12:48.028 --> 12:50.770
TWO, THREE, FOUR, ME,
JAKE, UH, SIX!

12:52.336 --> 12:53.729
THAT'S TWO MORE THAN YOU NEED.

12:53.860 --> 12:55.470
THE DEAL'S FOR SIX, PAL.

12:55.600 --> 12:56.906
COME ON.

12:57.037 --> 12:58.038
HAVE THEM COME.

12:58.168 --> 12:59.691
COME ON.

13:00.562 --> 13:01.563
COME ON, MAN.

13:01.693 --> 13:03.391
OKAY, I'LL DO IT.

13:03.521 --> 13:04.914
THINK OF IT, MITCH,

13:05.045 --> 13:06.960
YOU'RE GONNA BE THERE
AT THE START OF MY NEW CAREER.

13:07.090 --> 13:09.353
AND AT THE END OF IT. G'DAY!

13:09.484 --> 13:11.616
[CHEERING]

13:21.670 --> 13:22.845
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN, AGAIN,

13:22.976 --> 13:24.368
WE WOULD LIKE TO WELCOME YOU

13:24.499 --> 13:27.197
ABOARD AIR NEW ZEALAND'S
NON-STOP SERVICE TO SYDNEY.

13:27.328 --> 13:29.678
OUR MEAL SERVICE
WILL BEGIN SHORTLY,

13:29.809 --> 13:32.246
BUT IN THE MEANTIME,
WE'D LIKE YOU TO SIT BACK--

13:32.376 --> 13:33.769
HEY, I WAS WONDERING,

13:33.900 --> 13:36.250
WHY DIDN'T YOUR WIFE
TELL YOU ABOUT YOUR SON?

13:36.380 --> 13:39.731
I MEAN, SHE KNEW THAT SHE
WAS PREGNANT BEFORE YOU LEFT.

13:40.689 --> 13:42.256
WHY WOULD SHE KEEP IT FROM YOU?

13:44.258 --> 13:45.650
I DON'T KNOW.

13:47.652 --> 13:49.263
I GUESS SHE JUST STOPPED
LOVING ME.

13:50.220 --> 13:52.832
I MEAN, IT WAS JUST SUDDEN,
LIKE OUT OF THE BLUE.

13:55.356 --> 13:56.444
NOTHING'S OUT OF THE BLUE.

13:58.576 --> 14:00.143
MAYBE YOU JUST
DIDN'T SEE IT COMING.

14:04.104 --> 14:05.975
JESSIE,
IT'S REALLY NICE THAT YOU CARE.

14:10.893 --> 14:14.288
WHY DO YOU CARE? WE JUST MET.

14:21.121 --> 14:24.080
BECAUSE THAT LITTLE BOY WAS ME.

14:27.736 --> 14:30.304
I HAD A PAPER ROUTE
ON THE WEEKENDS,

14:30.434 --> 14:31.871
AND ON SUNDAYS
MY DAD WOULD HELP ME.

14:33.916 --> 14:35.570
WE'D GET UP REALLY EARLY,

14:35.700 --> 14:37.528
HAVE GLAZED DOUGHNUTS
FOR BREAKFAST,

14:37.659 --> 14:39.313
AND THEN WE'D HEAD OUT.

14:39.443 --> 14:42.316
WE'D SWING THOSE PAPERS FIRST
AT ONE DOOR, THEN THE OTHER.

14:44.622 --> 14:46.276
IT WAS MAGICAL TO ME.

14:50.324 --> 14:54.894
THEN ONE DAY WHILE I WAS
AT SCHOOL, HE LEFT.

14:55.938 --> 14:58.506
THERE WAS NO WARNING, NOTHING.

14:58.636 --> 15:01.335
FROM THAT MOMENT,
EVERYTHING IN MY LIFE CHANGED.

15:02.727 --> 15:04.599
I HAD TO MOVE IN WITH MY AUNT,

15:04.729 --> 15:06.557
DIFFERENT TOWN,
DIFFERENT SCHOOL.

15:08.342 --> 15:09.473
I NEVER REALLY FIT IN.

15:10.735 --> 15:13.477
MY MOM WENT
INTO A SEVERE DEPRESSION,

15:16.567 --> 15:17.742
AND, UH,

15:20.745 --> 15:22.182
SHE DIED A FEW YEARS LATER.

15:27.970 --> 15:29.276
DID YOU EVER HEAR
FROM YOUR DAD AGAIN?

15:30.146 --> 15:34.194
WELL, WE GOT A COLLECT
PHONE CALL FROM HIM

15:34.324 --> 15:35.456
THE DAY OF HER FUNERAL,

15:36.631 --> 15:38.546
BUT MY AUNT
WOULDN'T ACCEPT THE CHARGES.

15:40.461 --> 15:43.377
SO ANYWAY, WHEN THAT GUY CAME
INTO THE SHOWER,

15:43.507 --> 15:44.769
AND I SAW YOUR REACTION,

15:44.900 --> 15:46.554
WHEN HE TOLD YOU
THAT YOU HAD A SON,

15:48.295 --> 15:49.818
MY HEART BROKE.

15:50.732 --> 15:54.910
I COULDN'T HELP BUT THINK,
MAYBE MY DAD DIDN'T KNOW.

15:55.041 --> 15:57.739
HE KNEW, HE KNEW WHERE YOU WERE,
HE CALLED YOU.

15:59.001 --> 16:02.613
NO, WHAT I MEAN IS,
MAYBE HE DIDN'T KNOW

16:02.744 --> 16:04.659
HOW MUCH I REALLY NEEDED HIM.

16:05.790 --> 16:08.880
BECAUSE THERE WERE TIMES
WHEN I WAS SAD AND LONELY,

16:09.751 --> 16:11.535
OR TIMES WHEN I WAS BEING
PUSHED AROUND BY SOME BULLY,

16:11.666 --> 16:15.496
OR JUST LYING IN BED
AT NIGHT AFRAID OF THE DARK.

16:19.282 --> 16:21.893
I'D ALWAYS DREAM THAT MY DAD
WOULD COME AND SAVE ME,

16:25.767 --> 16:26.986
AND HE NEVER DID.

16:37.735 --> 16:38.432
I GET IT.

16:40.782 --> 16:41.957
DO YOU?

16:42.088 --> 16:43.176
YEAH.

16:45.395 --> 16:46.657
IT'S ABOUT HIM.

16:50.139 --> 16:51.358
THAT'S RIGHT.

17:03.370 --> 17:04.458
YOU KNOW WHAT APPEALS TO ME MOST

17:04.588 --> 17:05.849
ABOUT THIS TRIP?

17:05.981 --> 17:08.417
NO, BUT I GOT A FEELING
YOU'RE GONNA TELL ME.

17:08.549 --> 17:11.595
I'M NOT IN CHARGE, SOMEONE ELSE
IS DOING THE PLANNING,

17:11.726 --> 17:13.771
THE SCHEDULING, THE PERSONNEL.

17:13.902 --> 17:17.339
ALL I HAVE TO DO IS SIT BACK
AND BE PART OF THE TEAM.

17:18.559 --> 17:21.257
TOO MUCH ADMINISTRATION,
YOU KNOW?

17:21.387 --> 17:24.434
NOT ENOUGH SITTING
IN A TOWER WATCHING MY WATER.

17:29.004 --> 17:31.441
THESE ARE ALL THE SITES
FOR THE 2000 OLYMPICS,

17:32.660 --> 17:34.966
IT'S GONNA BE AMAZING.

17:35.097 --> 17:37.012
DOES IT GET YOU INSPIRED?

17:37.143 --> 17:38.753
YEAH.

17:38.883 --> 17:40.537
WELL,
ARE YOU GONNA TRY OUT AGAIN?

17:40.668 --> 17:42.974
MAKE THE OLYMPIC TEAM?
GO FOR THE GOLD?

17:43.105 --> 17:45.847
I MISSED MY CHANCE IN ATLANTA.

17:45.977 --> 17:47.762
