AVALON

25:59.122 --> 26:01.298
HELP! HELP HIM!

26:01.429 --> 26:02.865
SOMEBODY'S DROWNING!

26:02.996 --> 26:06.521
HELP HIM! HELP ME!

26:08.697 --> 26:12.745
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

26:13.789 --> 26:15.443
HELP!

26:19.142 --> 26:20.317
IAN!

26:23.494 --> 26:25.932
COME ON, GUYS, MOVE IT, QUICKLY.

26:27.411 --> 26:29.370
SOMEBODY'S DROWNING, HELP!

26:29.500 --> 26:33.853
HELP! HELP!

26:34.897 --> 26:36.159
SOMEBODY HELP!

26:51.653 --> 26:52.741
DON'T DO IT!

26:52.872 --> 26:55.178
DON'T! DON'T DO IT!

27:00.967 --> 27:03.622
IT'S TOO BIG!
IT'S TOO BIG TO GO IN!

27:03.752 --> 27:05.536
LET'S WAIT FOR A LOW!

27:11.717 --> 27:13.457
HELP, PLEASE, HE'S GONNA DROWN.

27:13.588 --> 27:15.285
YOU HAVE TO HELP HIM,
HE'S DROWNING.

27:15.416 --> 27:17.418
-HE FELL OFF THE ROCKS.
-IT'S ALL RIGHT.

27:23.511 --> 27:25.295
HERE COMES ANOTHER SWELL.

27:32.868 --> 27:34.740
OKAY, TRY NOW.

27:40.049 --> 27:41.660
SAVE HIM!

27:45.794 --> 27:47.013
HERE!

27:52.279 --> 27:54.847
NO, IT'S TOO BIG A WAVE,
WE'LL HAVE TO WAIT.

27:57.023 --> 27:59.852
HURRY! HURRY!

28:03.943 --> 28:06.075
COME ON, GET IN THERE.

28:07.947 --> 28:10.601
WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR,
HELP HIM!

28:22.048 --> 28:24.398
COME ON,
WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR?

28:25.616 --> 28:27.270
GET IN THERE AND HELP HIM!

28:31.405 --> 28:33.799
WHOA, BARELY MADE THAT.

28:38.368 --> 28:40.327
GET HIM, GET HIM IN!

28:44.026 --> 28:45.636
PULL HIM UP, COME ON, I GOTCHA.

28:49.771 --> 28:51.512
GOTCHA. I GOT YOU.

28:52.687 --> 28:53.688
GOT HIM.

28:54.558 --> 28:56.909
HURRY UP, IAN, LET'S GET OUT
OF HERE, COME ON.

29:00.260 --> 29:01.435
GO GO GO!

29:03.306 --> 29:04.438
LET'S STAND ASIDE.

29:04.568 --> 29:06.440
COME ON, LET'S GO MEET HIM.
WATCH YOUR STEP.

29:06.570 --> 29:07.441
OKAY.

29:07.571 --> 29:08.834
WATCH OUT.

29:16.667 --> 29:18.800
SURF RESCUE

29:21.934 --> 29:24.719
OH, ARE YOU OKAY?

29:24.850 --> 29:26.416
YOU'RE A LIFESAVER, RIGHT?

29:26.547 --> 29:27.766
LIFEGUARD, L.A. COUNTY.

29:27.896 --> 29:29.376
THAT WAS A CRAZY THING TO DO.

29:29.506 --> 29:31.552
WE DON'T GO OFF THE ROCKS
LIKE THAT!

29:31.682 --> 29:32.814
WHAT, YOU THOUGHT YOU COULD
SWIM 'EM OUT?

29:32.945 --> 29:34.598
HEY, LOOK,
THAT'S WHAT WE DO, PAL.

29:34.729 --> 29:35.643
WE GET OUR HANDS ON THE VICTIM,

29:35.774 --> 29:37.210
WE FIGURE IT OUT FROM THERE.

29:37.340 --> 29:38.646
IF I'M NOT HOLDING HIM UP,
IS HE STILL ALIVE

29:38.777 --> 29:39.690
BY THE TIME YOU GET THERE?

29:39.821 --> 29:43.259
HEY,
INTERESTING DON'T YOU THINK?

29:43.390 --> 29:45.348
ONE TECHNIQUE ALONE
WOULDN'T HAVE SAVED HIM,

29:45.479 --> 29:48.569
NOT YOURS, NOT OURS.

29:49.788 --> 29:51.224
WELL LOOK, WE SAVED HIM,

29:51.354 --> 29:52.703
AND THAT'S WHAT'S IMPORTANT,
OKAY?

29:52.834 --> 29:54.967
YEAH, WE GOT HIM
AND THAT IS WHAT'S IMPORTANT.

29:56.533 --> 29:59.841
HEY,
LET'S GET THOSE LOOKED AT, HUH?

30:08.632 --> 30:11.200
OH, JUST A COUPLE OF SCRATCHES,
NOTHING'S BROKEN.

30:12.593 --> 30:14.421
SO IS THIS
LIKE A LIFEGUARD HEADQUARTERS?

30:14.551 --> 30:18.773
YES AND NO, IT'S A CLUB,
ALMOST EVERY BEACH HAS ONE,

30:18.904 --> 30:21.341
VOLUNTEERS WHO PROTECT
OUR BEACHES.

30:21.471 --> 30:23.734
WE DO THE MAINTENANCE,
PAY THE BILLS,

30:23.865 --> 30:27.390
SWEEP THE FLOORS,
DO THE LAUNDRY, AND COOK.

30:27.521 --> 30:28.870
AND YOU WORK REGULAR SHIFTS?

30:29.001 --> 30:30.829
WE CALL THEM PATROLS, YEAH.

30:30.959 --> 30:32.091
WOW.

30:32.221 --> 30:33.875
SO, HOW DO YOU JOIN?

30:34.006 --> 30:35.834
HOW DID YOU BECOME A LIFEGUARD?

30:36.835 --> 30:38.097
PASSED A TEST.

30:38.880 --> 30:40.751
PROBABLY THE SAME KIND
OF TEST WE TAKE,

30:40.882 --> 30:44.451
AND IT'S MORE
THAN JUST PHYSICAL ABILITY.

30:44.581 --> 30:47.149
YOU HAVE TO KNOW YOU CAN DEPEND
ON ONE ANOTHER.

30:49.325 --> 30:50.413
EXACTLY.

30:51.458 --> 30:53.286
WHAT'S TERRY DOING HERE?

30:53.416 --> 30:54.504
CLAIRE WAS A MEMBER,

30:54.635 --> 30:57.899
BUT HE CAN'T CONTINUE TO STAY,
NOT ALONE.

30:58.030 --> 30:59.248
WHERE IS HE NOW?

31:01.468 --> 31:02.861
HE'S PROBABLY AT THE ROCK POOL.

31:05.124 --> 31:08.997
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

31:21.836 --> 31:24.186
HEY, HOW'S THE WATER?

31:24.317 --> 31:25.753
OKAY.

31:26.536 --> 31:27.842
IT'S WARM.

31:30.627 --> 31:31.802
WHAT'S YOUR DOG'S NAME?

31:31.933 --> 31:33.630
SPENCER.

31:33.761 --> 31:34.631
WHAT KIND IS HE?

31:34.762 --> 31:36.198
JUST DOG.

31:37.983 --> 31:39.245
WELL, THAT'S A GOOD KIND.

31:41.508 --> 31:43.292
WHAT'S HE DOING WAY OVER THERE?

31:43.423 --> 31:44.815
HE HATES TO GET WET.

31:57.002 --> 31:58.177
ARE YOU MY DAD?

32:00.657 --> 32:03.834
YES, TERRY, I'M YOUR DAD.

32:04.923 --> 32:07.316
SO, WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

32:07.447 --> 32:08.927
CALIFORNIA.

32:10.841 --> 32:13.888
WHEN I WAS A BABY, DID I DO
SOMETHING TO MAKE YOU ANGRY?

32:14.019 --> 32:15.368
IS THAT WHY YOU WENT AWAY?

32:15.498 --> 32:17.892
NO, NO, GOD, NO.

32:19.546 --> 32:20.634
UNTIL A COUPLE OF DAYS AGO,

32:20.764 --> 32:22.679
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
THAT YOU EXISTED, TERRY.

32:22.810 --> 32:24.638
WHY NOT?

32:24.768 --> 32:25.726
I DUNNO.

32:26.770 --> 32:29.860
MUM SAYS THAT "I DON'T KNOW"
IS NOT AN ACCEPTABLE ANSWER.

32:29.991 --> 32:33.690
YEAH, WELL I CAN HEAR YOUR MOM
SAY THAT.

32:35.170 --> 32:36.563
TERRY, YOUR MOM DIDN'T TELL ME
ABOUT YOU,

32:36.693 --> 32:37.651
AND I DON'T KNOW WHY,

32:38.521 --> 32:40.262
BUT SOMETIMES "I DON'T KNOW"

32:40.393 --> 32:42.395
IS THE ONLY ANSWER THAT I HAVE.

32:44.266 --> 32:45.746
SHE WOULD TELL ME
THINGS ABOUT YOU.

32:45.876 --> 32:48.140
OH YEAH? LIKE WHAT?

32:49.445 --> 32:50.533
HOW YOU MADE HER LAUGH.

32:51.404 --> 32:53.493
YEAH, YOUR MOM
AND I LAUGHED A LOT TOGETHER.

32:56.017 --> 32:58.324
TERRY, I'M REALLY SORRY
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED.

32:59.412 --> 33:01.109
I KNOW THAT YOU MISS HER A LOT,

33:01.718 --> 33:04.286
I KNOW THAT SHE LOVED YOU VERY,
VERY MUCH.

33:06.201 --> 33:07.637
ARE YOU GOING TO STAY WITH ME?

33:07.768 --> 33:12.077
YES, FOREVER,
AND THAT'S A PROMISE, OKAY?

33:19.127 --> 33:20.955
DO YOU WANT TO PLAY
UNDERWATER TAG?

33:22.217 --> 33:23.088
WHAT?

33:23.218 --> 33:25.220
TIP, YOU'RE IT.

33:32.923 --> 33:38.233
[LAUGHING]

33:51.638 --> 33:52.682
WELL, THEY'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

33:52.813 --> 33:55.381
WHY, BECAUSE THEY BOTH LIKE
THE WATER?

33:57.165 --> 33:58.340
IT'S A START.

34:11.962 --> 34:14.443
WELCOM TEAM BAYWATCH

34:14.574 --> 34:16.750
IT WAS GREAT FOR STAR CITY
TO PUT US UP, HUH?

34:16.880 --> 34:18.230
CHECK OUT THE VIEW!

34:18.360 --> 34:20.058
YEAH, THIS PLACE IS AWESOME.

34:20.188 --> 34:21.755
EVERYONE,

34:21.885 --> 34:24.018
IF I COULD HAVE A MOMENT
TO INTRODUCE OUR HOST

34:24.149 --> 34:26.716
AND SPONSOR OF OUR RACE,

34:26.847 --> 34:30.242
JOHN PAUL DEJORIA
AND HIS LOVELY WIFE, ELLOUISE.

34:30.371 --> 34:32.505
THANK YOU, THANK YOU.

34:32.635 --> 34:34.550
AND WE WOULD LIKE
TO WELCOME ALL OF YOU

34:34.681 --> 34:36.509
TO THE FIRST PAUL-MITCHELL
SYDNEY CHALLENGE.

34:36.639 --> 34:40.556
WE'RE VERY EXCITED TO HAVE
SUCH RESPECTED TEAMS

34:40.687 --> 34:41.688
ASSEMBLED INTO ONE--

34:41.818 --> 34:42.732
JP,
BEFORE YOU GO ANY FURTHER, I--

34:42.862 --> 34:44.342
LET HIM FINISH, BUDDY.

34:44.473 --> 34:46.475
THAT'S OKAY, MITCH, I'M USED
TO KIP INTERRUPTING ANYWAYS,

34:46.606 --> 34:47.868
KIP, THE FLOOR'S YOURS.

34:47.998 --> 34:49.913
I JUST WANT TO APOLOGIZE
TO MITCH.

34:50.043 --> 34:51.697
I ACCEPT. I PROPOSE A TOAST--

34:51.828 --> 34:53.960
YOU SEE, WHEN I SAID YOUR TEAM
DIDN'T HAVE A CHANCE

34:54.092 --> 34:58.183
AGAINST US,
I KNEW I HURT YOUR FEELINGS.

34:58.313 --> 35:01.403
IT'S JUST THAT YOU ARE
LIFEGUARDS, WHICH IS GREAT,

35:01.534 --> 35:03.971
BUT YOU'RE NOT REALLY ATHLETES,
WHICH IS ALL I MEANT TO SAY.

35:04.102 --> 35:05.929
NOT REALLY ATHLETES?

35:06.060 --> 35:07.540
NOT ATHLETES IN THE TRUE SENSE.

35:07.670 --> 35:08.671
DON'T CHASE IT, LET IT GO.

35:08.802 --> 35:09.933
NO, NO, NO,

35:10.064 --> 35:10.978
I DON'T LIKE
HIS CONDESCENDING ATTITUDE.

35:11.109 --> 35:12.240
ALEX.

35:12.371 --> 35:14.590
CODY HERE ALMOST MADE
THE US OLYMPIC TEAM.

35:15.461 --> 35:18.377
DUGO HERE WAS
ON THE AUSTRALIAN OLYMPIC TEAM.

35:18.507 --> 35:19.987
YOU SEE WHAT I MEAN?

35:20.118 --> 35:22.555
SO FAR THIS YEAR, HE'S BEEN
TWICE IN THE TOP 10 WORLDWIDE.

35:22.685 --> 35:25.732
DUGO, WAIT A MINUTE,
AS IN JAMES DUGAN?

35:26.646 --> 35:29.953
FREESTYLE SPRINTS, PERFECT.

35:30.780 --> 35:33.522
THIS BEAUTIFUL FEMALE SPECIMEN,
THIS IS NICKIE MASTERTON.

35:33.653 --> 35:34.654
SHE'S WON TWO TRIATHLONS.

35:34.784 --> 35:37.222
I CALL HER MY SILENT ASSASSIN.

35:37.352 --> 35:39.224
OH, PLEASE.

35:39.354 --> 35:41.878
AND THEN THERE'S KENDRA,
KENDRA'S A TIGER.

35:42.009 --> 35:44.011
SHE WAS LEADING THIS YEAR'S
WORLD KAYAK CHAMPIONSHIP,

35:44.142 --> 35:46.231
SHE WOULD HAVE WON,
BUT SHE SNAPPED A PADDLE.

35:46.361 --> 35:47.971
FINISHED WITH A STUB
AND STILL TOOK THIRD.

35:48.102 --> 35:49.930
WELL, MAYBE WE SHOULD LEAVE.

35:50.060 --> 35:51.671
THAT'S WHY I DIDN'T WANT
TO GET YOU SO INTIMIDATED

35:51.801 --> 35:53.063
YOU LOSE HEART.

35:53.194 --> 35:54.413
CAN I DO MY TOAST NOW?

35:54.543 --> 35:56.023
-PLEASE, WILL YOU?
-THANK YOU.

35:56.154 --> 35:58.939
TO JP
AND HIS LOVELY WIFE ELLOUISE,

35:59.069 --> 36:01.768
THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR THIS OPPORTUNITY.

36:01.898 --> 36:05.119
AND TO OUR OPPONENTS, WITH THE
HOPE, THE WORDS SPOKEN TODAY,

36:05.250 --> 36:07.600
MAY NOT BE
TOO HARD TO SWALLOW TOMORROW.

36:07.730 --> 36:09.123
CHEERS.

36:19.133 --> 36:21.266
AVALON BEACH

36:24.530 --> 36:25.487
[KNOCKING]

36:25.618 --> 36:27.010
HEY, BUDDY, WHAT'S GOING ON?

36:29.012 --> 36:30.579
HEY, THIS IS A PRETTY COOL ROOM.

36:31.885 --> 36:33.278
OH, YOU LIKE SURFING?

36:33.408 --> 36:35.802
OH YEAH, YEAH AFTER SCHOOL

36:35.932 --> 36:37.456
I'M NORMALLY OUT THERE
IN THE WAVES.

36:37.586 --> 36:39.197
YEAH? DO YOU LIKE SCHOOL?

36:40.459 --> 36:41.677
MM, SOME OF IT.

36:41.808 --> 36:43.549
WHAT'S YOUR FAVORITE SUBJECT?

36:43.679 --> 36:44.637
HISTORY.

36:44.767 --> 36:46.682
MINE TOO. COOL.

36:46.813 --> 36:48.206
SO, WHAT ARE YOU STUDYING NOW?

36:48.641 --> 36:49.946
OH, EARLY SETTLERS.

36:50.077 --> 36:51.774
YEAH? THE PILGRIMS.

36:51.905 --> 36:53.341
PILGRIMS WERE PRETTY BRAVE,
DON'T YOU THINK?

36:54.124 --> 36:55.517
WHO?

36:55.648 --> 36:58.694
THE PILGRIMS, YOU KNOW?
PLYMOUTH ROCK, THANKSGIVING.

36:59.347 --> 37:00.479
WE DON'T STUDY THEM.

37:01.131 --> 37:03.351
NO, RIGHT,
OF COURSE YOU WOULDN'T.

37:04.091 --> 37:05.223
YOU GOT A GIRLFRIEND?

37:07.790 --> 37:10.140
OKAY, HOW ABOUT SPORTS?

37:10.271 --> 37:11.533
WHAT'S YOUR FAVORITE SPORT?

37:12.404 --> 37:13.274
CRICKET.

37:13.405 --> 37:15.276
CRICKET IS YOUR FAVORITE SPORT?

37:15.407 --> 37:16.538
AFTER FOOTIE.

37:16.669 --> 37:20.325
FOOTIE? OH, FOOTBALL, YEAH,
I LOVE FOOTBALL.

37:20.455 --> 37:22.805
YEAH, I LOVE FOOTBALL, YEAH.

37:23.806 --> 37:25.199
WHAT'S THAT SMELL,
SOMETHING SMELLS AWESOME.

37:25.330 --> 37:27.070
IT'S A SAUSAGE SIZZLE.

37:27.201 --> 37:28.724
A WHAT?

37:29.551 --> 37:31.684
A SAUSAGE SIZZLE.

37:33.033 --> 37:34.861
YOU HAVE THE COOLEST ACCENT.

37:35.731 --> 37:37.603
I DON'T HAVE AN ACCENT, YOU DO.

37:37.733 --> 37:40.997
TELL ME ONE MORE TIME,
WHAT ARE WE GONNA EAT?

37:41.694 --> 37:43.522
A SAUSAGE SIZZLE.

37:43.652 --> 37:45.915
OH, I LOVE THE WAY
THAT YOU SAY THAT.

37:47.482 --> 37:49.354
LOOK, I'M GONNA GO DOWNSTAIRS,

37:49.484 --> 37:50.572
DO YOU WANNA COME WITH ME?

37:51.225 --> 37:52.661
YEAH, I'LL BE DOWN IN A SECOND,

37:52.792 --> 37:53.880
I'VE JUST GOTTA GO GET SPENCER.

37:54.010 --> 37:57.405
OKAY. SAUSAGE SIZZLE...

38:00.495 --> 38:01.844
IT'S A COOL ROOM.

38:05.457 --> 38:07.241
THAT WAS SO MUCH FUN.

38:07.372 --> 38:08.677
IT'S SUCH A BEAUTIFUL DAY.

38:08.808 --> 38:09.678
I KNOW, HUH?

38:09.809 --> 38:10.766
[SCREAMING]

38:10.897 --> 38:12.333
OH, IS HE A GREAT KID OR WHAT,
HUH?

38:12.464 --> 38:13.595
YEAH.

38:13.726 --> 38:15.336
OH, THANK YOU, THANK YOU
FOR ALL YOUR BACKUP.

38:15.467 --> 38:16.642
YOU'RE WELCOME.

38:16.772 --> 38:19.340
AND ALLIE, THANK YOU
FOR TAKING CARE OF HIM.

38:19.471 --> 38:22.082
OH, I HAVE EVERYTHING
I COULD EVER WISH FOR.

38:23.213 --> 38:24.345
EXCEPT CLAIRE.

38:26.782 --> 38:28.480
I WISH SHE WERE HERE.

38:33.746 --> 38:34.573
HEY, GOOD LUCK TOMORROW.

38:34.703 --> 38:35.878
YOU TOO.

38:38.490 --> 38:40.883
I WISH I WASN'T SO SHY.

38:41.014 --> 38:42.755
YOU DON'T SEEM SHY TO ME.

38:42.885 --> 38:44.496
I AM, PAINFULLY.

38:45.671 --> 38:47.325
WELL, THAT'S TOO BAD.

38:47.455 --> 38:50.110
I KNOW, BECAUSE,
IF I WASN'T SO SHY,

38:50.240 --> 38:52.547
I WOULD BE ABLE TO TELL YOU
HOW BEING THIS CLOSE TO YOU

38:52.678 --> 38:53.679
MAKES MY HEART RACE.

38:56.682 --> 38:58.205
I'M GONNA WALK AWAY NOW.

38:58.336 --> 38:59.380
DID I MAKE YOU ANGRY?

38:59.511 --> 39:01.382
NO, YOU JUST CONFUSED ME.

39:01.513 --> 39:04.342
EITHER YOU'RE THE SWEETEST,
MOST INGENUOUS GUY

39:04.472 --> 39:06.256
I'VE EVER MET, OR...

39:07.388 --> 39:08.215
OR?

39:08.346 --> 39:10.043
OR YOU'RE NOT.

39:12.045 --> 39:14.003
EXCUSE ME, GUYS, THANKS
FOR AN AWESOME PARTY, HUH?

39:14.134 --> 39:16.049
-ARE YOU LEAVING?
-YEAH, JET LAG.

39:16.179 --> 39:17.920
OH, I UNDERSTAND.
GOOD LUCK TOMORROW.

39:18.051 --> 39:19.618
OKAY, THANKS AGAIN.

39:22.795 --> 39:24.274
THANK YOU VERY MUCH,
I APPRECIATE THAT,

39:24.405 --> 39:25.275
THAT WAS GREAT.

39:25.406 --> 39:26.494
THANK YOU, GOOD LUCK.

39:26.625 --> 39:28.366
THANK YOU, WE'RE GONNA NEED IT,
THANKS.

40:20.940 --> 40:25.074
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

40:31.777 --> 40:33.126
I'M GONNA GET YOU
SOME MORE TO EAT.

40:37.522 --> 40:38.740
HEY, HOW DO YOU LIKE IT HERE?

40:38.871 --> 40:40.829
ARE YOU KIDDING ME,
THIS PLACE IS GREAT.

40:40.960 --> 40:43.615
WELL, IF YOU'RE GONNA STAY,
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO Q.

40:43.745 --> 40:44.572
Q?

40:44.703 --> 40:45.791
AS IN QUALIFY,

40:45.921 --> 40:47.967
PASS A PHYSICAL TEST
FOR MEMBERSHIP.

40:48.097 --> 40:49.359
NO, NO, NO, THANK YOU,

40:49.490 --> 40:50.752
BUT AS SOON AS I GET
TERRY PACKED,

40:50.883 --> 40:53.146
HE AND I ARE GOING HOME,
BACK TO CALIFORNIA.

40:53.276 --> 40:58.325
[SAD MUSIC PLAYING]

42:15.750 --> 42:19.750
[ENDING MUSIC]
